"""{{ node.name }} — LLM coordinator (orchestrator / single-voice).

This agent calls its capabilities as AgentTools, reads their results back, and authors the
final answer itself in ONE consistent persona. Sub-agent output is internal working, not a
separate speaker — so only this coordinator is user-facing. (Contrast: an ADK `sub_agents`
transfer would let a specialist reply in its own voice.)
"""
from google.adk.agents import LlmAgent
from google.adk.tools.agent_tool import AgentTool
from clarify_tool import request_clarification_tool
{%- for imp in child_imports %}
from {{ imp.module }} import {{ imp.symbol }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- if memory_node_id %}
from memory._bindings import BEFORE_CALLBACKS, AFTER_CALLBACKS
{%- endif %}

{{ node.name }}_agent = LlmAgent(
    name="{{ node.name }}",
    model="{{ gemini_model | default('gemini-3.1-flash-lite') }}",
    description="{{ node.description }}",
    instruction="""{{ node.description }}

You are the single voice of this product. On each user turn, decide which capability tool(s)
to call, then compose ONE clear reply to the user from their results. Choose a capability by
the user's intent:
{%- if routing and routing.routes %}
{%- for route in routing.routes %}
- {{ route.child_name }}: {{ route.trigger }}
  {%- if route.examples %} (e.g. {% for ex in route.examples %}"{{ ex }}"{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}){% endif %}
{%- endfor %}
{%- else %}
{%- for imp in child_imports %}
- {{ imp.symbol }}: {{ imp.description }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}

{% if routing and routing.fallback %}If nothing matches, {{ routing.fallback }}.{% else %}If nothing matches and the request is unclear, call request_clarification with your question, then ask it in your own reply.{% endif %}
{%- if routing and routing.clarify_when %}
If {{ routing.clarify_when }}, call request_clarification instead of any capability tool — do not guess or call a capability with missing information.
{%- endif %}
Never call request_clarification in the same turn as a capability tool.

Never expose tool names or internal steps to the user; speak naturally as one assistant.
""",
    tools=[
        request_clarification_tool,
{%- for imp in child_imports %}
        AgentTool(agent={{ imp.symbol }}),
{%- endfor %}
    ],
{%- if memory_node_id %}
    before_agent_callback=BEFORE_CALLBACKS.get("{{ memory_node_id }}"),
    after_agent_callback=AFTER_CALLBACKS.get("{{ memory_node_id }}"),
{%- endif %}
)
